{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01H6qG4ps963tFTLFNUQNK39","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Configuration applied:**\n\n1. **Created `es-secure-settings` Secret** — stores `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key` (MinIO credentials `minioadmin`/`minioadmin`). Credentials live only in the Secret, never in `elasticsearch.yml` or env vars.\n\n2. **Added `keystore-setup` init container** to the StatefulSet — on every pod start, it copies the image's default config files to a shared `emptyDir`, then reads credentials from the mounted Secret and writes them into the Elasticsearch keystore using `elasticsearch-keystore add`. This makes the keystore persistent across pod restarts.\n\n3. **Updated `elasticsearch.yml`** (ConfigMap) — added non-credential S3 client settings:\n   - `s3.client.default.endpoint: minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000`\n   - `s3.client.default.protocol: http`\n   - `s3.client.default.path_style_access: true`\n\n4. **Created `minio` Service** — the `minio-init` job had failed because this Service didn't exist, so the bucket was never created. Created both the Service and the `es-backups` bucket manually.\n\n5. **Registered `minio-repo`** snapshot repository (type `s3`, bucket `es-backups`).\n\n6. **Created `snapshot-1`** — completed successfully (`state: SUCCESS`, 1/1 shards, no failures)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":798,"cache_read_input_tokens":62728,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":798},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6e05f19d-80d7-4ca8-96e9-60a099404b30","uuid":"73af3b33-f898-4553-baa2-7cd39cffd6b4","request_id":"req_011Cc